  - Chapter completion tracking
- [x] LevelManager script (loads chapter data, spawns enemies, tracks objectives)
- [x] Main scene updated for dynamic chapter loading
- [x] Dialogue system — typewriter effect, tap/click/space advance
  - DialogueManager as CanvasLayer + PackedScene
  - Triggers: "start" (blocks combat until dialogue ends), "objective_complete"
  - Shows "[TAP TO CONTINUE]" on mobile, "[PRESS SPACE / CLICK]" on desktop
- [x] Chapter 002: "The Merchant's Plea" — JSON + MD design doc added
  - Merchant ally NPC (with follow_distance, dialogue entries)
  - Weapon unlock flow (steel_dagger)
  - Continues chapter chain (act01_ch003)
- [x] Chapter completion flow now loads next chapter data properly
  - Unlocks next chapter in GameState
  - Objective label shows "CHAPTER COMPLETE — Press R to continue"

### Architecture
Swordjin_Godot/
├── project.godot              # Autoloads: GameState, ChapterDatabase
├── scenes/
│   ├── main.tscn             # LevelManager + player + walls + DialogueManager
│   ├── player.tscn           # CharacterBody2D, attack hitbox
│   ├── skeleton.tscn         # Enemy AI with detection + attack
│   ├── mobile_controls.tscn  # Touch joystick + buttons
│   └── dialogue_manager.tscn # CanvasLayer (Panel, Labels)
├── scripts/
│   ├── autoload/
│   │   ├── game_state.gd     # Save/load, progression
│   │   └── chapter_database.gd # JSON chapter loader
│   ├── player.gd             # Input, combat, HP
│   ├── skeleton.gd           # Chase AI, attack, death
│   ├── level_manager.gd      # Chapter setup + objective tracking + dialogue
│   ├── mobile_controls.gd    # Touch input mapping
│   └── dialogue_manager.gd   # Typewriter dialogue system
└── chapters/
    └── act01/
        ├── chapter001.json   # Data (enemies, dialogue, rewards)
        ├── chapter001.md     # Design doc
        ├── chapter002.json   # Merchant ally, steel dagger unlock
        └── chapter002.md     # Design doc

